cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper discusses auto-encoding and generative models for image and signal representation learning, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new approach to capturing the manifold structure of data, which involves parameterizing the data set as a collection of overlapping charts, which is a concept from differential geometry. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SD), which often incorporate mathematical concepts from differential geometry.
